---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="About"
  description="Full-stack engineer who builds from idea to production — Vue 3, Cloudflare Workers, GraphQL, and AWS."
>
  <article class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-20">
    <!-- Page header -->
    <header class="mb-16">
      <p class="text-accent-light text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">Hey, I'm Luís.</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Full-stack engineer who likes to own things end-to-end — from the first design
        decision to the deploy button and whatever comes after.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
      <!-- Main content -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-12">
        <!-- Philosophy -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">How I work</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              I like to stay close to the whole problem. That means I'll design the API
              and write the component that calls it, set up the infrastructure and be the
              one who investigates when something goes sideways.
            </p>
            <p>
              Not because I need to do everything, but because the gaps between layers
              are usually where things go wrong — and I'd rather own those gaps than
              hand them off and hope for the best.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Background -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Background</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              I've spent most of my career in B2B and platform products, working across
              the stack — Vue 3 on the frontend, Cloudflare Workers at the edge, GraphQL
              Federation for APIs, and AWS for the bits underneath.
            </p>
            <p>
              I'm most comfortable when I can move across all of those layers without
              context-switching overhead. That's usually where I add the most value.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Current focus -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Right now</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Experimenting with AI-assisted engineering and how agent-driven workflows
              can take on real delivery work. This portfolio was built with one.
            </p>
            <p>
              Available for consulting where speed and full-stack ownership matter.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar: quick facts -->
      <aside class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-text-muted mb-4">Expertise</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {[
              'Vue 3',
              'Cloudflare Workers / BFF',
              'GraphQL + Federation',
              'AWS infrastructure',
              'CI/CD pipelines',
              'Data migration',
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 text-text-secondary text-sm">
                <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent-light flex-shrink-0"></span>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-text-muted mb-4">Connect</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <a href="https://github.com/LuisZMarques" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
               class="flex items-center gap-2 text-text-secondary hover:text-accent-light text-sm transition-colors focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-accent-light focus-visible:outline-offset-2 rounded">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
              </svg>
              github.com/LuisZMarques
            </a>
            <a href="/contact"
               class="flex items-center gap-2 text-text-secondary hover:text-accent-light text-sm transition-colors focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-accent-light focus-visible:outline-offset-2 rounded">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 8l7.89 4.26a2 2 0 002.22 0L21 8M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"/>
              </svg>
              Get in touch
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
